A jet of flames erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a precise part of the forest ablaze, then circled above it for a while, observing. Curiously, as he had slowed down, the strange cries behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I'm not lifted abruptly by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not that bad, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly didn't agree with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had dug his claws into Thassalin's back so deeply that they had wounded the Thraki, but obviously, he didn't care much about it. Still, Thassalin realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing where to land.
"MY SORRY, I SMELLED SOMETHING. I HAD TO CHECK."
"You had to drag us here with you?" Tenuk asked as he slid down from Thassalin's back along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big and strong fighter! How will he catch up with us?"
"He'll find a way," replied Nissy. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive something as cute as Kayel's little car either. And if he started coming to work by car at all, it's only because YOU drove us there. He just has that bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly hysterical, and no one understood what made him laugh. It took him too long to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED MY GRAND FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINIATURE CHILDREN'S BIKE. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WISH I HAD TELEPATHY. IT'S A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and briefly disappeared before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I SMELL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND CHASE. AS YISINI DEMANDS. CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. So did Nyssi and Kayel, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something big and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, paying no mind to the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just barely, but Nyssi was dragged and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the aggression by catching Nyssi and throwing her onto his back using his extraordinarily long and agile tail before taking off. The two-winged black creature rushed after them quickly.
Kayel sighed, drawing the gun from his back, then opened a pouch containing a belt of ammunition. He slung it over his shoulder to make accessing it easier, but soon realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that flies?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra-powerful gun in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself some space. In a low growl slightly embarrassed, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms turned into wings. He quickly became the usual light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Having returned to a more normal Thraki form, Tenuk now had scales covering his back, but a pair of spikes had also grown there, making it practical for Kayel to grip onto. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk narrowly avoided it.
I suppose it's the other scary big monster that Lanex was worried about? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot at the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on heading towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel awkwardly did a spin in mid-air to face the monster. The fact that it was pursuing them was good for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature, which screamed in pain before disappearing again under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it certainly wouldn't be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi desperately clung on, while Thassalin flew in circles, shooting bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature clearly seemed injured, it appeared furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took advantage to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. Of course, it wasn't meant for such situations, but a burst of fire would surely at least deter the black beast, right?
